===Etymology===
The name ''Afghan'' is believed to have derived from [[Sanskrit]] ''Ashvakan'', meaning "horseman". The suffix ''stan'' has the meaning ''"land"'' in [[Persian]], so that ''Afghan + stan'' = Afghanistan, or "land of Afghans." See [[w:List of country name etymologies|Wikipedia article on Etymology of Afghanistan]].

===Pronunciation===
*Af'ga'nis'tan

===Proper noun===
'''Afghanistan'''
#a country in Central [[Asia]]. Official name: Afghanistan. Capital: [[Kabul]]. Official languages: [[Persian]] ([[Dari]]), [[Pashto]].

